{"profile":{"awsPrograms":[{"joinedAt":2026.0,"programName":"USER_GROUP_LEADER"},{"category":"Security Hero","joinedAt":2024.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"HERO"}],"basicInfo":{"alias":"pigius","avatar":"https://avatars.builderprofile.aws.dev/2yUt3Wo6smfx2uO7kMdHDRxzUQO.webp","bio":"Daniel Aniszkiewicz – Wrocław, Poland\n\nSecurity Hero Daniel Aniszkiewicz is a software engineer with over 10 years  of experience in building, architecting, and securing production-grade  systems on AWS. His focus spans cloud security architecture, fine-grained  authorization, serverless and event-driven systems, and agentic AI systems  on AWS - combining hands-on engineering with architectural problem solving.\n\nDaniel co-organizes the AWS User Group Wrocław, contributing to the growth  and engagement of the local AWS community for years. He is a seasoned  conference speaker with multiple appearances at AWS re:Invent in Las Vegas,  AWS re:Inforce (including a joint session with the Amazon Verified  Permissions service team), AWS Summits in the Netherlands and Dubai, and  AWS Community Days in Poland and Prague.\n\nHis technical work focuses on Amazon Verified Permissions, Cedar policy  language, automated reasoning, fine-grained authorization, Amazon Bedrock  and AgentCore, serverless and event-driven architecture,  OpenTelemetry-based observability, and the security architecture of  agentic AI systems on AWS. \n\nDaniel shares his work through workshops, blog  posts, IaC templates, and open source projects.","builderProfileId":"9a4d8009-ad2c-44c2-b1b9-ba92d2a3b484","createdOn":1.717850734592E12,"isStaff":false,"name":"Daniel Aniszkiewicz"},"location":{},"profileStatus":"ACTIVE","socials":{}}}